Circular Dependencies are usually a sign of bad design and should be avoided, as you correctly mentioned. To improve your design you might want to get familiar with the SOLID principles. Especially, the Single Responsibility Principle. 

From your description, ServiceB seems to be doing more than one thing. It validates your event and makes sure a ServiceC is called to created a new event. Instead you could have both ServiceB and ServiceC as dependencies of ServiceA. That would get rid of your circular dependency. Maybe this helps: 

    void process(Event event) {
      if(!serviceB.isValid(event)) {
        Event correctedEvent = serviceC.correctEvent(event);
        processValidEvent(correctedEvent);
      }
      processValidEvent(event);
    }

